{
  "stem": "17135.5",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was full of [INAUDIBLE], like the one that went to California when California was discovered.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This Volksdeutsche, this ethnic Germans, they're running away from the-- from the-- from the Russians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know there were-- there were Volksdeutsche in Hungary, in Romania, in Poland, and they were the first target.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When the Russians conquered a city, they shot them on the spot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were considered traitors, and they ran away from them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I mixed among them, because that was it an advantage.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I spoke German.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was only chaos, let me put it this way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The SS was panicking, because the Russians were chasing them day and night.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were on their way to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and-- and the Germans didn't ask me for papers, the-- the-- the ethnic Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They gave me food, whatever they had.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What I didn't know is that every kilometer was a checkpoint with SS men and-- and German soldiers, and they recruited anybody from the age of 16 to 60 in the army, because there weren't enough soldiers, and I got twice in order to present myself to be recruited.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now can you imagine?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They see my number, and see I'm circumcised, that is death on the spot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my luck was, while I was in Germany in a gymnasium, they study.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Seven years Latin, four years French, three years English, and if you had a-- a-- a-- a-- how you call it-- a-- a career in the-- in the humanities, you have to learn Greek also.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So anyway, I had a knack for French, for some reason, and many French Jews in '43 came to Auschwitz, they were [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They knew Yiddish, but they spoke only French, so I'm in it with them and-- and just [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
